---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Privacy policy — ADE Showdown">
  <article class="policy">
    <p class="policy__eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h2>ADE Showdown privacy policy</h2>
    <p>
      ADE Showdown uses GitHub OAuth through Supabase Auth so one GitHub account can save one
      rating per feature. The application table stores only your Supabase user UUID, feature IDs,
      ratings from 1 to 5, and update timestamps.
    </p>
    <h3>Data we process</h3>
    <p>
      Supabase Auth may store your GitHub account identifier, email, and handle as part of the
      authentication record. Those identity fields are not copied into the `ratings` business table
      and are not exposed publicly by row-level security.
    </p>
    <h3>Processors</h3>
    <p>
      Hosting runs on Cloudflare Pages. Authentication and database storage run on Supabase in the
      Frankfurt EU region for production projects. GitHub provides OAuth authentication.
    </p>
    <h3>Legal basis and retention</h3>
    <p>
      Ratings are saved after explicit consent through GitHub sign-in and the consent checkbox before
      the first vote. Data is kept until you delete your account or request removal.
    </p>
    <h3>Your rights</h3>
    <p>
      Use the <a href="/account">account page</a> to export your data or delete your account and all
      saved ratings. The export includes your account metadata (email, identities, sign-in timestamps),
      your ratings, and your skipped features. Account deletion calls a Supabase Edge Function which
      deletes the Supabase Auth user; the `ratings` and `feature_skips` rows are removed by the
      database cascade.
    </p>
    <p>
      When you delete your account, an anonymized audit row containing only a technical identifier
      (your former Supabase UUID, no longer linked to any account) and a timestamp is retained for
      up to 12 months for security and abuse-detection purposes. This log contains neither email,
      IP address, nor any other data that could identify you.
    </p>
    <h3>Cookies and analytics</h3>
    <p>
      ADE Showdown does not use third-party analytics. Supabase session storage is used only for
      authentication and is treated as strictly necessary technical storage.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .policy { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .policy__eyebrow { margin: 0 0 8px; color: var(--accent); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.18em; font: 700 0.75rem var(--font-display); }
  h2 { margin: 0 0 18px; font: 900 clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem)/1 var(--font-display); text-transform: uppercase; }
  h3 { margin-top: 26px; }
  p { color: var(--fg-soft); }
</style>
